President Obama has nominated Judge Brian R. Martinotti and Robert F. Rossiter, Jr. to serve on the United States District Courts. Judge Martinotti has served on the Superior Court of New Jersey since 2002 and has experience in handling mass torts and other types of cases. Robert F. Rossiter, Jr. is a partner at Fraser Stryker PC LLO in Omaha, Nebraska, specializing in labor and employment litigation. He has been with the law firm since 1983 and has served on its Management Committee since 2011. Both nominees have had distinguished legal careers and are expected to serve the American people with distinction from the District Court bench.